<h1 style="font-size: 60px; color: green;text-align: left; padding-top: 95px;">AROMATHERAPY</h1>
   </div>
 <details style="background-color: #f5deb3">
 	<summary>Precautionary measures while using Aromatherapy</summary>
 	<p>To do an allergy test:<br>
Dilute the essential oil in a carrier oil at twice the concentration you plan to use<br>
Rub the mixture into an area the size of a quarter on the inside of the forearm </p>
 </details>

<div class="div1">
<div class="body">  
<h2 class="headi">WHAT IS MEANT BY AROMATHERAPY?</h1>  
<p class="font">Aromatherapy is a holistic healing treatment that uses natural plant extracts to promote health and well-being. Sometimes it’s called essential oil therapy. Aromatherapy uses aromatic essential oils medicinally to improve the health of the body, mind, and spirit. It enhances both physical and emotional health.</p>
<h2 class="headi">BENEFITS OF AROMATHERAPY</h2>
<p>
<dl>
  <dt>PROVIDES ENERGY</dt>
  <dd>Essential oils that can invigorate the senses, and give you that pep in your step. All citrus oils, especially lemon, are filled with antioxidant terpenes such as limonene, which have naturally energizing effects.</dd>
  <dt>REDUCES STRESS</dt>
  <dd>The essential oils and massage are scientifically proven to reduce stress.They calm the nervous system, lower blood pressure, heart rate, and rewires brain waves to help you become more relaxed.</dd>
  <dt>RELIEVES ANXIETY</dt>
  <dd> Long-term stress can cause a wide variety of health problems if it goes unaddressed. Essential oil, in its oil form, is clinically proven to reduce stress when used properly.</dd>
  <dt> STRENGTHENS YOUR IMMUNE SYSTEM</dt>
  <dd>Due to their anti-inflammatory properties, essential oils are useful when it comes to fighting infections. For example, oregano is known for its antiviral and antibacterial properties that protect the body against bacterial infections.
  </dd>
</dl>
</p>
<h2 class="headi">HOW AROMATHERAPY WORKS ?</h2>
<p>aromatherapy activates areas in your nose called smell receptors, which send messages through your nervous system to your brain.

The oils may activate certain areas of your brain, like your limbic system, which plays a role in your emotions. They could also have an impact on your hypothalamus, which may respond to the oil by creating feel-good brain chemicals like serotonin.when you put essential oils on your skin, they cause a response in your skin and other parts of your body, like your joints.<,p>

<h2 class="headi">HOW TO GET STARTED WITH THE SERVICE?</h2>
<p>there are numerous online classes and tutorials that can walk you through the basics of using essential oils. You may also be able to find courses in your community or professionals who specialize in the field who you can meet with in person to discuss your questions.
Or consider making an appointment with a licensed professional for a relaxing massage or other treatment if you’re looking for stress relief. 
You don’t have to invest a lot of time or money to try out aromatherapy. If you want to start slow, consider picking a popular scent, such as lavender, and applying a few drops to your wrists and temples. Slowly breathe in the scent and see if it helps stress melt away.</p>
<h2 class="headi">CAUTIONS WHILE CHOOSING ESSENTIAL OILS</h2>
<ul>
 <li>Concentrated products may be poisonous before dilution and should be handled with care. A maximum concentration of 5 percent is recommended.</li>
 <li>Some oils produce toxins which can cause damage to the liver, kidneys, and nervous system, especially if taken internally</li>
 <li>Swallowing essential oils can be hazardous, and fatal in some cases.</li>
 <li>A person with high blood pressure, for example, should avoid stimulants, such as rosemary.</li>
 <li>Some compounds, such as fennel, aniseed, and sage act similarly to estrogen.Thus,they should be used accordingly.</li>
<p></p>
